The United States OT/IoT Grid Edge Sensor and Monitoring for Real-Time Grid Visibility market size was valued at USD 1.19 billion in 2026. The market is projected to grow from USD 1.28 billion in 2026 to USD 2.32 billion by 2034, exhibiting a CAGR of 8.9% during the forecast period.
OT/IoT grid edge sensors are specialized devices that deliver real‑time monitoring of electrical‑grid parameters at the distribution edge, enabling enhanced visibility, predictive maintenance, and automated control. These sensors include voltage and current transducers, frequency meters, power‑quality analyzers, and advanced communication modules that transmit data over secure IoT networks.
